gnm:Cells.gnm:Cell: This table contains a structured mechanism for calculating coordinates by measured values (S-distance, Z-zenith angle, B-horizontal direction) by modifying the conformal transformation of the 1st degree (linear).
CATALOG sheet - catalog of starting points (Y, X, H)
POINTS sheet - measurement results (S, Z, B, hp) and processing result (Y, X, H) and the corner elements (a, Z*) for the Geodesic Linear intersection.
WORK sheet - basic calculations (if there is no failure, do not go there)
SITER sheet - an iterative mechanism for estimating unmeasured distances (requires additional recalculation <F9>)
SCHEME sheet - graphical representation of the network and the result
HOW TO: Angles in measurement results are presented in degrees with decimal places (as in most electronic total station files).
HOW TO: All unmeasured distances in the measurement results are represented as 0, or less than 0. For such distances, the SITER mechanism is automatically activated.
WARNING: If your table has unmeasured distances (<= 0), then press <F9> (recalculation) multiple times to ensure an iterative process.
WARNING: If SITER fails, save the table, reopen and recalculate (<F9> - multiple times).
